ADAPTATION PROCESS

When adapting code from the above projects, the following process is
followed (documented in docs/adr/002-code-acquisition-strategy.md):

1. LICENSE CHECK  — Verify source license permits adaptation
2. COPY           — Bring source files into the Credo directory structure
3. ATTRIBUTE      — Retain original copyright headers in each file
4. ADAPT          — Rename packages, update imports, align with Credo conventions
5. SIMPLIFY       — Remove code not needed for Credo's architecture
6. TEST           — Adapt and run original tests, add new ones
7. DOCUMENT       — Update this NOTICES file and doc.go

Over time, adapted code is expected to diverge substantially from its
origin as Credo's own patterns and requirements evolve. This file records
the initial provenance for transparency and legal compliance.
